 "lrc": "[00:00.00]Voice 1 - Raspy:\n[00:00.00]Ayo...\n[00:00.00]Voice 1:\n[00:00.00]Don’t touch that hat.\n[00:00.00]Voice 2 - Crazy Whisper:\n[00:00.00]Heh... too late.\n[00:00.00]Both:\n[00:00.00]Brooms in the boiler room.\n[00:00.00]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[00:30.32]water starts to rise,\n[00:31.52]little mouse grinning with the stars in his eyes.\n[00:33.92]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[00:35.28]knocking at the door,\n[00:36.32]spell got loose and it hungry for more.\n[00:38.72]Black-and-white world,\n[00:39.84]but the money still gold,\n[00:41.20]whole tower shaking when the wild drums roll.\n[00:43.76]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[00:45.04]moon turned blue,\n[00:46.24]one wrong spell and the whole crew doomed.\n[00:48.64]I came through small with the hat pulled low,\n[00:51.04]stars on the brim and the gloves still glow.\n[00:53.52]Strings go stab,\n[00:54.72]bassoon go low,\n[00:55.76]broom got a bucket and it march like woah.\n[00:58.40]Told me don’t touch,\n[00:59.52]so I touched that quick,\n[01:00.64]now the whole tower sick and the floorboards shift.\n[01:03.20]One broom, two brooms,\n[01:04.72]three more rise,\n[01:05.76]black ink magic in the cartoon eyes.\n[01:08.32]Timpani boom when the stairwell crack,\n[01:10.72]oboe line howlin’ and the shadows clap back.\n[01:13.28]Moonlight bends when the wand goes snap,\n[01:15.60]shadow on the wall with a long-eared cap.\n[01:17.92]I ain’t scared,\n[01:19.04]I’m just deep in the trick,\n[01:20.64]too much power for a little dude slick.\n[01:22.80]Black-and-white frame,\n[01:24.08]but the gold still gleam,\n[01:25.52]money in the fog and the magic in steam.\n[01:28.24]Voice 1:\n[01:28.40]Who cast that?\n[01:29.60]Voice 2:\n[01:29.92]Not me.\n[01:30.03]Voice 1:\n[01:30.13]Who touched the hat?\n[01:31.04]Voice 2:\n[01:31.92]Not me.\n[01:32.00]Voice 1:\n[01:33.12]Who flooded the room?\n[01:36.24]Voice 2:\n[01:36.24]Couldn’t be me.\n[01:37.24]Both:\n[01:37.92]Then why the broom got a whole army?\n[01:37.92]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[01:39.12]water starts to rise,\n[01:40.32]little mouse grinning with the stars in his eyes.\n[01:42.80]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[01:44.08]knocking at the door,\n[01:45.12]spell got loose and it hungry for more.\n[01:47.68]Black-and-white world,\n[01:48.72]but the money still gold,\n[01:50.08]whole tower shaking when the wild drums roll.\n[01:52.64]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[01:53.84]moon turned blue,\n[01:55.04]one wrong spell and the whole crew doomed.\n[01:57.12]I seen the mop grow teeth in the midnight haze,\n[01:59.68]seen buckets pour rivers through a hundred stairways.\n[02:02.40]Woodwinds laughing,\n[02:03.60]trumpets go crooked,\n[02:04.64]whole magic tower looking haunted and flooded.\n[02:07.20]Old wizard gone,\n[02:08.32]but the hat stayed watching,\n[02:09.92]every little sparkle turned toxic.\n[02:12.32]Broomstick army with the wooden-leg stomp,\n[02:14.56]tap dance terror when the bassline thump.\n[02:16.96]I told little homie,\n[02:18.16]“You don’t know that spell.”\n[02:19.28]He said,\n[02:19.60]“I know enough to make the whole room swell.”\n[02:21.84]Then the strings start chasing,\n[02:23.36]ceiling got eyes,\n[02:24.56]stars in the robe started falling from the sky.\n[02:27.12]Cauldron bubble,\n[02:28.08]floorboards split,\n[02:29.60]one more chant and the whole place flipped.\n[02:31.76]Magic ain’t cute when the shadows get tall,\n[02:34.32]especially when the mouse got control of it all.\n[02:44.08]Voice 1 - Raspy:\n[02:44.36]They said he was just an apprentice.\n[02:47.76]Voice 2 - Laughing:\n[02:48.48]Apprentice?\n[02:49.04]Voice 1:\n[02:49.56]Yeah.\n[02:50.11]Voice 2:\n[02:51.81]Then why the broom saluting him?\n[03:02.00]Both:\n[03:02.43]Brooms...\n[03:02.82]in the boiler room.\n[03:09.36]Voice 1:\n[03:09.76]Hat too big.\n[03:10.72]Voice 2:\n[03:11.20]Spell too strong.\n[03:12.32]Voice 1:\n[03:12.32]Broom too wild.\n[03:13.20]Voice 2:\n[03:15.68]Night too long.\n[03:16.32]Voice 1:\n[03:17.52]Water too high.\n[03:18.15]Voice 2:\n[03:19.68]Door won’t move.\n[03:20.40]Voice 1:\n[03:21.03]Whole tower drowning.\n[03:21.97]Voice 2:\n[03:22.59]Still in groove.\n[03:23.53]Voice 1:\n[03:24.18]Strings go sharp.\n[03:25.29]Voice 2:\n[03:25.87]Bassoon go doom.\n[03:26.06]Voice 1:\n[03:26.18]Timpani hit.\n[03:26.72]Voice 2:\n[03:26.93]Oboes fill the room.\n[03:27.47]Voice 1:\n[03:27.75]One little mouse.\n[03:28.16]Voice 2:\n[03:28.43]Big mistake.\n[03:28.71]Voice 1:\n[03:28.98]One little wand.\n[03:29.39]Voice 2:\n[03:29.67]Whole world shake.\n[03:30.08]Both:\n[03:30.22]Black-and-white world but the money still gold,\n[03:31.60]whole crew slipping while the spell takes hold.\n[03:33.92]No crown, no throne,\n[03:35.12]just a hat and a grin,\n[03:36.32]then the broomsticks rise and the nightmare begins.\n[03:41.04]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[03:45.36]water starts to rise,\n[03:46.48]little mouse grinning with the stars in his eyes.\n[03:49.04]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[03:50.32]knocking at the door,\n[03:51.28]spell got loose and it hungry for more.\n[03:54.16]Black-and-white world,\n[03:54.88]but the money still gold,\n[03:56.32]whole tower shaking when the wild drums roll.\n[03:58.80]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[04:00.16]moon turned blue,\n[04:01.36]one wrong spell and the whole crew doomed.\n[04:08.80]Brooms in the boiler room,\n[04:10.16]still marching,\n[04:11.44]still stomping,\n[04:12.72]still pouring,\n[04:13.92]still watching.\n[04:18.40]Voice 2:\n[04:23.28]You think it’s over?\n[04:26.24]Voice 1:\n[04:27.04]Nah.\n[04:28.00]Voice 2:\n[04:29.74]Why?\n[04:29.81]Voice 1:\n[04:29.94]The hat still glowing.\n"
